programme.desc: When an ex-convict returns home to solve his sister's murder, the authority forces him to go undercover to help them bust illegal activities at a nightclub.

programme.title: Hollywood On Set
programme.desc: The host sheds light on the making of various films, giving the behind-the-scenes updates from movie sets and interacting with actors and crew members. USA 2003.

programme.title: Hollywood On Set
programme.desc: The host sheds light on the making of various films, giving the behind-the-scenes updates from movie sets and interacting with actors and crew members. USA 2003.

programme.title: Hollywood On Set
programme.desc: The host sheds light on the making of various films, giving the behind-the-scenes updates from movie sets and interacting with actors and crew members. USA 2003.

programme.title: Mune
programme.desc: When a group of evildoers steal the sun, the guardians of the moon and the sun set out on a journey to fight against the group and retrieve the sun.

programme.title: Fallen
programme.desc: Detective John Hobbes witnesses the execution of a demonic serial killer, Edgar Reese. However, the killings resume and are very similar to the style of Reese.

programme.title: Land Of The Bears
programme.desc: The filmmaker observes the mannerisms, daily activities and adventures of five wild brown bears in the Kamchatka Peninsula.

programme.title: The Magnificent Ruffians
programme.desc: Lu Feng recruits four out of work kung fu experts from another town to harass Lo Mang and take over his business. However, his plan backfires and they become friends with Lo Mang.

programme.title: TMNT
programme.desc: Follows the adventures of the four teenage mutated turtles gifted in the art of the ninja, as they attempt to stop a mysterious evil that threatens to end the world.

programme.title: Mr. & Mrs. Smith
programme.desc: A husband and wife struggle to keep their marriage alive until they realise they are both secretly working as assassins. Now, their respective assignments require them to kill each other.

programme.title: The Last Witch Hunter
programme.desc: A never dying witch hunter is compelled to confront the Witch Queen again after tracking down her henchmen for centuries.

programme.title: Mirrors
programme.desc: Ben guards a partly destroyed property during the nights but begins to see strange images in its impeccable mirrors. After his sister is killed, he is convinced that evil forces are out to get him.

programme.title: Five Superfighters
programme.desc: Three kung fu students are determined to avenge their master after being beaten by a stranger and venture out to learn new skills in pursuit of revenge.

programme.title: Cloudy With A Chance Of Meatballs
programme.desc: Flint Lockwood, an inventor who is considered a nuisance, puts his latest invention to work when his town faces an economic crisis. His invention makes him popular until it spirals out of control.

programme.title: The Twilight Saga: Breaking Dawn - Part 1
programme.desc: After consummating her marriage with Edward, Bella realises that she has become pregnant with a child that is half-human, half-vampire. Further, the unborn child has many enemies in the outside world.

programme.title: Piranha 3D
programme.desc: After an earthquake splits a lake floor, a swarm of ancient piranhas are released. A group of strangers come together to stop themselves from becoming the victims of these deadly predators.

programme.title: Love Is In The Air
programme.desc: Antoine, a lawyer from New York, travels to France for the final round of a job interview. On the flight, he is seated next to Julie, his ex-girlfriend, with whom he has to make awkward conversation.

programme.title: About Last Night
programme.desc: Danny and Debbie pretend to be a couple for a night. The next day, they decide to test how well their relationship works in the real world.

programme.title: All The Pretty Horses
programme.desc: While travelling to Mexico to find work, John Grady Cole, a Texan cowboy, finds himself in trouble as he encounters love, corruption and passion.

programme.title: The Night Before
programme.desc: Ethan, Isaac and Chris are best friends who have celebrated every Christmas Eve together. Things take a turn when Isaac and Chris decide to end their decade-long tradition.

programme.title: Vanguard
programme.desc: Qin, an accountant living in the UK, is targeted by the leader of a terrorist organisation. His only hope for survival is Vanguard, an elite security company.

programme.title: Flower Shop Mystery: Snipped In The Bud
programme.desc: Abby happens to meet her old rival while delivering a bouquet of roses ordered by an anonymous person. However, things get worse when the man is later found dead and all evidence points to Abby.

programme.title: Peninsula
programme.desc: A former soldier along with his teammates sets out on a mission to battle hordes of post-apocalyptic zombies in the Korean peninsula wastelands.

programme.title: The Green Hornet
programme.desc: After his father's death, Britt inherits the largest media company in Los Angeles. He teams up with Kato to fight crime but ends up becoming the target of an underworld don, Benjamin Chudnofsky.

programme.title: Baby Geniuses
programme.desc: Two evil scientists hold babies as captives in their laboratory in order to crack the code to baby talk. However, one of the infants escapes and attempts to rescue the rest with some help.

programme.title: The Exorcist III
programme.desc: Lieutenant Kinderman sets out to investigate a series of brutal murders with the trademark of a serial killer, The Gemini. However, he uncovers disturbing facts which leave him troubled.

programme.title: Hunt For The Wilderpeople
programme.desc: Ricky Baker runs away to the wild when his foster mother dies. However, his cantankerous uncle Hector joins him and gets to know him better on their way out of the wild.

programme.title: Stealing Harvard
programme.desc: John Plummer ventures into the world of crime when he needs to raise money for his niece's admission to Harvard University. However, things turn awry after the police pursue the conman.

programme.title: Insidious: The Last Key
programme.desc: Parapsychologist Elise Rainier gets thrust into returning to her eerie childhood home where she and her family have to fight a dangerous otherworldly entity.

programme.title: Step Brothers
programme.desc: Two men without any aim in life are compelled to share a room and live under one roof after their parents get married to each other.

programme.title: Midwives
programme.desc: A well-to-do midwife in rural Vermont finds her life turned upside down when she gets accused of murdering one of her patients by the woman's husband.

programme.title: Excess Baggage
programme.desc: Emily fakes her own kidnapping in order to get her father's attention. She locks herself in the trunk of a car, but the situation changes when a thief steals the car with her inside.

programme.title: You Got Served
programme.desc: Elgin and David begin a dance crew that engages in dance battles at a local club. But tensions begin to brew when Wade challenges them to a dance-off for a big cash prize.

programme.title: La Bamba
programme.desc: Ritchie Valens, a teenage Mexican migrant, becomes an overnight rock 'n' roll star. As his star begins to ascend, he must deal with his brother's envy and the constant nightmares of a plane crash.

programme.title: The Wedding Ringer
programme.desc: Doug Harris is getting married in two weeks and has no groomsmen because of his social awkwardness. He calls the owner of Best Man Inc for help and forms an unlikely bond with him.

programme.title: Peninsula
programme.desc: A former soldier along with his teammates sets out on a mission to battle hordes of post-apocalyptic zombies in the Korean peninsula wastelands.

programme.title: Fight To the Finish
programme.desc: Sean, an amateur fighter, interferes in the personal life of a hardened criminal. When the criminal threatens his life, Sean decides to settle the matter in a fighting tournament.

programme.title: Hotel Mumbai
programme.desc: A hotel staff risks everything to keep its patrons safe during a terror attack, especially a British heiress, her husband and her infant.

programme.title: Miss Bala
programme.desc: Gloria gets abducted by a group of criminals when she visits Mexico to meet her friend Suzu. Later, she uses her wit to survive in the cruel world of crime.

programme.title: Good Luck Chuck
programme.desc: Chuck, a dentist, discovers that women inevitably find their soul mate immediately after having a sexual encounter with him. But it poses a problem when he falls in love with Cam.

programme.title: Identity
programme.desc: Stranded at a desolate motel during a nasty rainstorm, ten strangers become acquainted with each other. However, they soon realise that they are being killed off one by one.

programme.title: Conspiracy
programme.desc: A retired US Marine Sergeant decides to visit an old friend in the South West. However, when he arrives, he finds his friend missing and no one in town admits knowing him.

programme.title: Anatomy
programme.desc: Paula, a medical student, wins a place in a summer course at a renowned hospital. During her stint at the hospital, she discovers a secret society that performs gruesome experiments on humans.

programme.title: Vacancy
programme.desc: A couple stuck at a secluded motel see that several video cameras are attached to their room. They realise that unless they flee, they will become the next victims of a snuff film.

programme.title: Philadelphia
programme.desc: A young Philadelphia lawyer who is infected with AIDS keeps his homosexuality hidden from his employers. When he is suddenly dismissed, he hires a homophobic lawyer for a wrongful dismissal suit.

programme.title: What Makes A Family
programme.desc: To keep the custody of her daughter, Janine fights an uphill battle against the family of the woman whom she loved, who had birthed their child and lost her life soon after.

programme.title: The Exorcism Of Emily Rose
programme.desc: Reverend Moore performs an exorcism on a girl believed to be possessed by demons. The prosecutor argues that the girl suffered from schizophrenia, but Moore's defence lawyer has a different opinion.
